-- Zambian Kwacha Heads for Strongest Close Since November
-- B y   M a t t h e w   H i l l
-- 2012-07-04T16:06:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/zambian-kwacha-heads-for-strongest-close-since-november.html
Zambia’s kwacha gained 2.6 percent
against the dollar, heading to its strongest close in nearly
eight months.  The currency of  Africa ’s biggest copper producer advanced
the most since September 27 to trade at 5,034 a dollar by 6:04
6:04 p.m. in Lusaka. Earlier it traded as high as 5,014 per
dollar, its strongest level since Nov. 9.  To contact the reporter on this story:
